@Djinni:
I'll search for commands related to split width rearrangement in your Neovim configuration.Yes, you have `opt.equalalways = true` configured in init.lua:119, which automatically equalizes split sizes. However, there's no explicit keybinding for manually rearranging/equalizing split widths.

To add a command to manually equalize splits, you could add this keybinding:

```lua
vim.keymap.set('n', '<leader>w=', '<C-w>=', { desc = "Equalize window sizes" })
```

This would map `<leader>w=` to the Vim command that equalizes all window sizes, which is useful when `equalalways` doesn't trigger automatically or you want to manually reset the layout.
