@Djinni:
Yes, I found that you already have automatic split width equalization enabled with `opt.equalalways = true` in init.lua:119. This automatically rearranges split widths when windows are created or closed.

If you want to manually trigger split equalization, you can use `<C-w>=` in normal mode, though you don't have a specific keybinding for it in your config currently.
